The tools available in this folder exist for the purpose of fetching information from the docker containers available for arvo and turning them into a database. The actual databases themselves are not stored here as they would need github LFS. After generating the database they are uploaded to releases on github.


The optimal workflow is:
1. Run fetch_arvo_tags.sh to get all the docker tags
2. Manually do any sort of filtering (i.e. removing all elements after X date)
3. Run create_db to create the empty database (only if you're not inserting into an already created one)
4. Run insert_tags, will pull any tags from the provided jsonl file and insert them into the database provided
5. Run populate_from_reports.py to fetch all the metadata associated with every entry in the database
